It is hereby stipulated that if the Lessee defaults in the payment of rent for a period of 5 consecutive months, the Lessor shall have the right, in addition to other rights and remedies available under this Lease Deed and applicable laws, to initiate legal proceedings for recovery of dues and possession of the Leased Premises, in addition to claiming damages for breach of contract, yuuuug88ug89kbjbijb.
clause44: 4.4. However, the Lessor must provide written notice to the Lessee of its intention to enforce the penalty specified in clause 4.3. If the Lessee settles the overdue rent within 5 days from the issuance of the notice by the Lessor, the Lessor shall not have the right to enforce the penalty. Conversely, if the Lessee fails to pay the overdue rent within 5 days from the date of the notice issued by the Lessor, the Lessor may proceed to take the actions specified in clause 4.3 above.
